<br>
I interact with the evil side of Norrath, but I have my own reasons for doing that.  For a lot of people, role-playing interaction between good and evil means having nothing to do with the opposite side of that coin whenever possible.  Perhaps you don't consider that very interesting, and perhaps it isn't what you would like to see, but it's still a valid form of role-playing.  Lots of people would consider an all alignment trade fair to be very inappropriate for their character concepts.  When was the last time you read about Jews and Muslims coming together on the West Bank to have a bake sale?  (and no, I'm not suggesting one or the other is Good and the other Evil.  It's just an example)<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm not trying to rain on the idea.  I'm just objecting to the suggestion that people who aren't RPing Good/Evil interaction in this way aren't role-playing.<br>
<br>
Beyond that, and I've made this point a lot of times in the past, if you want an event you have to go through certain steps to make one happen.  Talk to guild and friends, pick an appropriate time and spot, and advertise it.  Posting on public boards that &quot;We need to have more of X&quot; might get a few people agreeing with you (and you've had that) but it isn't going to make something happen.  Come up with exact details, put in the work yourself if you have the initiave to see this through, and perhaps something will come of it.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
